C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Iran%20allows%20Indian%20officials%20to%20meet%2017%20Indians%20onboard%20seized%20vessel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713161975000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109304324%2Cimgsize-694385.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fafter-jaishankars-call-iran-allows-indian-officials-to-meet-17-indians-onboard-seized-vessel%2Farticleshow%2F109304226.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fafter-jaishankars-call-iran-allows-indian-officials-to-meet-17-indians-onboard-seized-vessel%2Farticleshow%2F109304226.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Is%20Dry%20Promotion%3F%20New%20Job%20Trend%20That%20Employees%20Aren't%20Thrilled%20About%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20ever-evolving%20landscape%20of%20the%20global%20job%20market%20has%20seen%20several%20trends%20over%20the%20decades.%20From%20work%20from%20home%20to%20shared%20working%20space%2C%20the%20list%20is%20endless.%20Now%2C%20we%20have%20a%20new%20phenomenon%20that%20is%20quietly%20gaining%20prominence%20-%20%E2%80%9Cdry%20promotion%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDry%20promotion%20refers%20to%20the%20practice%20of%20bestowing%20employees%20with%20a%20job%20promotion%20with%20no%20increase%20in%20salary.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20while%20your%20title%20changes%2C%20your%20workload%20grows%2C%20and%20your%20responsibilities%20increase%2C%20you%20do%20not%20receive%20any%20monetary%20compensation%20for%20these%20changes%20that%20the%20promotion%20brings%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20report%20by%20compensation%20consultant%20Pearl%20Meyer%20revealed%20that%20more%20than%2013%25%20of%20employers%20chose%20to%20give%20their%20employees%20new%20job%20titles%20instead%20of%20money.%20This%20number%20was%20only%208%25%20in%202018%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Flifestyle%2Fcareers%2Fthat-new-job-comes-with-a-bigger-title-and-no-raise-whats-your-move-b79c919d%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20a%20survey%20of%20900%20companies%20by%20benefits-advisory%20firm%20Mercer%20found%20that%20more%20employers%20are%20assigning%20less%20of%20their%202024%20salary%20budgets%20for%20promotion-related%20hikes%20when%20compared%20to%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20employees%20may%20not%20be%20thrilled%20by%20this%20trend%2C%20the%20growing%20practice%20is%20also%20considered%20by%20experts%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20average%20worker's%20diminishing%20bargaining%20power.%20These%20promotions%20tend%20to%20become%20more%20prevalent%20during%20periods%20of%20economic%20uncertainty%20with%20companies%20focussing%20on%20cost-cutting%20measures.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20companies%20faced%20with%20labour%20shortages%20were%20often%20compelled%20to%20offer%20substantial%20raises%20to%20retain%20employees.%20However%2C%20the%20trend%20of%20dry%20promotion%20has%20come%20at%20a%20time%20when%20some%20employers%20are%20redistributing%20the%20responsibilities%20of%20laid-off%20workers%20to%20existing%20staff%20members%20without%20increasing%20their%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvidence%20of%20the%20trend%20is%20also%20visible%20on%20social%20media%2C%20with%20several%20employees%20sharing%20their%20experience%20with%20such%20offers.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20a%20Reddit%20thread%20shared%20last%20year%2C%20a%20user%20revealed%20that%20their%20manager%20told%20them%20that%20since%20they%20work%20more%20than%20a%20junior%20usually%20does%2C%20the%20management%20had%20%E2%80%9Cdecided%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20junior%20in%20my%20title%E2%80%9D.%20The%20user%20shared%3A%20%E2%80%9CHowever%20when%20I%20asked%20how%20that%20impacts%20my%20salary%2C%20they%20said%20not%20at%20all%2C%20it%20stays%20exactly%20the%20same%20for%20this%20year.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-embed-height%3D%5C%22316%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Fcareerguidance%2Fcomments%2F11jbodx%2Fpromotion_but_no_salary_increase%2F%5C%22%3EPromotion%20but%20no%20salary%20increase%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cnby%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fuser%2FKufff%2F%5C%22%3Eu%2FKufff%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Fcareerguidance%2F%5C%22%3Ecareerguidance%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EOffering%20advice%2C%20one%20user%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20only%20thing%20a%20better%20title%20will%20do%20with%20no%20additional%20money%20is%20help%20you%20find%20a%20better%20job%20somewhere%20else.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20user%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20company%20is%20low%20on%20resources%2C%20and%20rather%20than%20actually%20hiring%20for%20open%20positions%2C%20they%20just%20spread%20the%20outstanding%20responsibilities%20among%20existing%20employees%20and%2For%20move%20employees%20around%20the%20organisation%20to%20meet%20their%20needs%20without%20increasing%20headcount%20or%20expense.%20Leverage%20this%20new%20title%20bump%20to%20make%20a%20lateral%20move%20at%20another%20company.%20Run%20away%20as%20fast%20as%20you%20can.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20title%20is%20not%20the%20recognition.%20The%20salary%20increase%20is%20the%20recognition.%20The%20only%20way%20to%20make%20big%20jumps%20in%20salary%20and%20at%20market%20value%20is%20to%20go%20somewhere%20that'll%20pay%20you%20more.%20If%20you%20stay%20where%20you%20are%2C%20they'll%20only%20incrementally%20give%20you%20pay%20raises...then%20after%205%20or%206%20years%2C%20you%20are%20below%20market%20rate%2C%E2%80%9D%20explained%20another%20user.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20look%20for%20a%20new%20job%2C%20some%20also%20suggested%20that%20employees%20might%20request%20flexible%20working%20schedules%2C%20extra%20paid%20time%20off%2C%20or%20additional%20benefits%20to%20compensate%20for%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20raise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713161880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-01%2Fk89fgov_office-generic_625x300_08_January_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-dry-promotion-new-job-trend-that-employees-arent-thrilled-about-5444706%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ever-evolving%20landscape%20of%20the%20global%20job%20market%20has%20seen%20several%20trends%20over%20the%20decades.%20From%20work%20from%20home%20to%20shared%20working%20space%2C%20the%20list%20is%20endless.%20Now%2C%20we%20have%20a%20new%20phenomenon%20that%20is%20quietly%20gaining%20prominence%20-%20%26quot%3Bdry%20promotion%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-dry-promotion-new-job-trend-that-employees-arent-thrilled-about-5444706%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-dry-promotion-new-job-trend-that-employees-arent-thrilled-about-5444706%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-dry-promotion-new-job-trend-that-employees-arent-thrilled-about-5444706%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20election%3A%20Can%20Trump%20still%20become%20president%20if%20convicted%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713161644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109304159%2Cimgsize-974175.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-election-can-trump-still-become-president-if-convicted%2Farticleshow%2F109304134.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F109304134.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%2C%20the%20presumptive%20Republican%20Party%20nominee%20for%20the%20November%202024%20US%20presidential%20election%2C%20is%20no%20stranger%20to%20the%20courtroom.%20In%20January%202024%2C%20a%20jury%20in%20New%20York%20ruled%20that%20he%20would%20have%20to%20pay%20writer%20E.%20Jean%20Carroll%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20damages%20for%20sexually%20abusing%20and%20then%20defaming%20her%2C%20a%20decision%20that%20Trump%20is%20appealing.%20That%20was%20a%20civil%20case.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-election-can-trump-still-become-president-if-convicted%2Farticleshow%2F109304134.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-election-can-trump-still-become-president-if-convicted%2Famp_articleshow%2F109304134.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-election-can-trump-still-become-president-if-convicted%2Famp_articleshow%2F109304134.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BNeed%20To%20Safeguard%20Judiciary%26quot%3B%3A%20Retired%20Judges%20Write%20To%20Chief%20Justice%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%2021%20retired%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20high%20courts%20have%20written%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20on%20the%20escalating%20attempts%20by%20%26quot%3Bcertain%20factions%20to%20undermine%20the%20judiciary%20through%20calculated%20pressure%2C%20misinformation%2C%20and%20public%20disparagement%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20critics%20are%20motivated%20by%20narrow%20political%20interests%20and%20personal%20gains%20and%20are%20striving%20to%20erode%20public%20confidence%20in%20the%20judicial%20system%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20retired%20judges%2C%20including%20four%20from%20the%20top%20court%2C%20did%20not%20specify%20the%20incidents%20which%20prompted%20them%20to%20write%20to%20the%20CJI%2C%20their%20letter%20came%20amid%20amid%20a%20war%20of%20words%20between%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20and%20opposition%20parties%20over%20the%20actions%20against%20some%20opposition%20leaders%20in%20corruption%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20affected%20leaders%20and%20their%20parties%20moving%20courts%20to%20seek%20relief%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20often%20accused%20them%20of%20using%20judicial%20decisions%20selectively%20and%20cited%20any%20lack%20of%20relief%20for%20several%20arrested%20leaders%20to%20rebut%20the%20opposition's%20criticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20retired%20judges%2C%20including%20justices%20(retired)%20Deepak%20Verma%2C%20Krishna%20Murari%2C%20Dinesh%20Maheshwari%20and%20M%20R%20Shah%2C%20accused%20the%20critics%20of%20having%20insidious%20methods%20with%20clear%20attempts%20to%20sway%20judicial%20processes%20by%20casting%20aspersions%20on%20the%20integrity%20of%20courts%20and%20the%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuch%20actions%20not%20only%20disrespect%20the%20sanctity%20of%20our%20judiciary%20but%20also%20pose%20a%20direct%20challenge%20to%20the%20principles%20of%20fairness%20and%20impartiality%20that%20judges%2C%20as%20guardians%20of%20the%20law%2C%20have%20sworn%20to%20uphold%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said%20in%20the%20letter%20titled%20%26quot%3BNeed%20to%20safeguard%20judiciary%20from%20unwarranted%20pressures%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20strategy%20employed%20by%20these%20groups%20is%20deeply%20troubling%2C%20ranging%20from%20the%20propagation%20of%20baseless%20theories%20intended%20to%20malign%20the%20judiciary's%20reputation%20to%20engaging%20in%20overt%20and%20covert%20attempts%20to%20influence%20judicial%20outcomes%20to%20their%20favour%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20behaviour%2C%20we%20observe%2C%20is%20particularly%20pronounced%20in%20the%20cases%20and%20causes%20of%20social%2C%20economic%20and%20political%20significance%2C%20including%20the%20cases%20involving%20certain%20individuals%2C%20wherein%20the%20lines%20between%20advocacy%20and%20manoeuvring%20are%20blurred%20to%20the%20detriment%20of%20judicial%20independence%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20writers%20said%20they%20are%20particularly%20concerned%20about%20the%20tactics%20of%20misinformation%20and%20the%20orchestration%20of%20public%20sentiment%20against%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20practice%20of%20selectively%20praising%20judicial%20decisions%20that%20align%20with%20one's%20views%20while%20vehemently%20criticising%20those%20that%20do%20not%2C%20undermines%20the%20very%20essence%20of%20judicial%20review%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20urged%20the%20judiciary%20led%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20fortify%20against%20such%20pressures%20and%20ensure%20that%20the%20sanctity%20and%20autonomy%20of%20the%20legal%20system%20are%20preserved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20imperative%20that%20the%20judiciary%20remains%20a%20pillar%20of%20democracy%2C%20immune%20to%20the%20whims%20and%20fancies%20of%20transient%20political%20interests%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713161640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fa4oahjjg_cji-dy-chandrachud_625x300_09_March_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fretired-judges-write-to-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-need-to-safeguard-judiciary-5444441%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20group%20of%20retired%20judges%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20high%20courts%20have%20written%20to%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20on%20escalating%20attempts%20by%20%26quot%3Bcertain%20factions%2