's%20employee%20to%20access%20company%20secrets%20and%20replicate%20products%20from%20the%20grocer%3A%20WSJ%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20and%20Trader%20Joe's%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661c60b81caec1275a6ffd4c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20compete%20with%20other%20major%20grocery%20stores%20including%20Trader%20Joe's.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Keeble%2FGetty%20Images%2C%20Michael%20Siluk%2FUCG%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIn%202016%2C%20Amazon%20launched%20a%20private-label%20brand%2C%20Wickedly%20Prime%2C%20to%20compete%20with%20Trader%20Joe's.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20hired%20a%20former%20senior%20manager%20at%20Trader%20Joe's%20snack%20division%2C%20per%20WSJ.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20employee%20was%20hounded%20for%20data%20on%20Trader%20Joe's%20best-selling%20snacks%20and%20margins%20for%20each%20product.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Amazon%20team%20that%20was%20developing%20the%20online%20giant's%20private-label%20food%20brand%2C%20Wickedly%20Prime%2C%20repeatedly%20pressured%20an%20ex-Trader%20Joe's%20senior%20manager%20for%20data%20that%20could%20help%20the%20company%20compete%20with%20the%20popular%20grocer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fretail%2Famazon-the-everything-war-dana-mattioli-4966915d%3Fmod%3Dhp_lead_pos7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Amazon%20launched%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Famazon-wickedly-prime-snack-food-products-2017-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWickedly%20Prime%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20sells%20an%20assortment%20of%20food%20and%20snacks%20like%20roasted%20cashews%20and%20garlic%20mustard%20aioli.%20The%20project%20was%20just%20one%20of%20a%20few%20ways%20Amazon%20was%20entering%20the%20food%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Journal%2C%20Amazon%20appeared%20to%20have%20a%20model%20it%20wanted%20to%20replicate%20for%20Wickedly%20Prime%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrader-joes-fans-explain-psychology-why-they-love-store-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrader%20Joe's%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20company%20hired%20a%20former%20senior%20manager%20from%20the%20grocery%20store's%20snack%20foods%20division.%20The%20Journal%20reported%20that%20she%20was%20told%20only%20after%20being%20recruited%20that%20her%20role%20was%20to%20help%20create%20a%20product%20line%20for%20Amazon's%20private%20label.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20Amazon%20wanted%20to%20replicate%20the%20top%20200%20items%20sold%20at%20Trader%20Joe's.%20Because%20this%20data%20is%20not%20readily%20available%2C%20an%20Amazon%20manager%20repeatedly%20hounded%20the%20ex-Trader%20Joe's%20employee%20%E2%80%94%20who%20is%20not%20named%20in%20the%20Journal's%20article%20%E2%80%94%20for%20six%20months%20over%20data%20on%20the%20store's%20top%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20former%20Trader%20Joe's%20employee%20gave%20up%20the%20requested%20data%20after%20the%20manager%20demanded%20that%20she%20hand%20over%20any%20emails%20and%20documents%20she%20preserved%20from%20her%20time%20with%20the%20grocer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Amazon%20manager%20also%20pressed%20the%20ex-Trader%20Joe's%20employee%20for%20data%20on%20the%20margins%20for%20each%20product.%20She%20refused%2C%20and%20the%20manager%20resorted%20to%20yelling%20at%20the%20employee%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Journal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20just%20have%20to%20give%20us%20the%20data!%26quot%3B%20the%20manager%20yelled%2C%20according%20to%20a%20source%20who%20saw%20the%20interaction%20and%20recalled%20it%20to%20the%20news