Url%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22BBC%20Verify%20examines%20video%20from%20Iran's%20attack%20on%20Israel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713130800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FC945%2Fproduction%2F_133152515_verifythumbnail.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-68814427%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Footage%20shows%20projectiles%20being%20intercepted%20after%20Iran%20attacked%20Israel%20with%20drones%20and%20missiles.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fav%2Fworld-middle-east-68814427%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20was%20a%20consultant%20at%20McKinsey.%20Here's%20the%20frustrating%20way%20they%20pushed%20me%20out.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222624%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ezra%20Gershanok%2C%20Ohana%20founder%2C%20ex-McKinsey%20analyst%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661c155c3f923f7dab07c4c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221968%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEzra%20Gershanok%20is%20a%20former%20Business%20Analyst%20at%20McKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company.%3Cp%3EEzra%20Gershanok%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EEzra%20Gershanok%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-burnout-quit-elitist-consulting-lifestyle-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebusiness%20analyst%20at%20McKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20he%20was%20forced%20out%20as%20the%20firm%20grappled%20with%20declining%20client%20demand%20and%20too%20many%20hires.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPost-McKinsey%2C%20Gershanok%20co-founded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fliveohana.ai%2Fhomeowners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOhana%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20sublet%20startup%20backed%20by%20Zillow%20and%20Airbnb's%20execs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20conversation%20with%20Ezra%20Gershanok%2C%20a%20former%20Business%20Analyst%20at%20McKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%20and%20the%20cofounder%20of%20sublet%20startup%20Ohana.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELong%20story%20short%2C%20I%20don't%20regret%20my%20time%20at%20McKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20hired%20straight%20out%20of%20college%20as%20a%20Business%20Analyst%2C%20an%20entry-level%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsultant-analyst-guide-common-corporate-job-titles-project-manager-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsultant%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20firm.%20I'm%20glad%20I%20had%20the%20opportunity%2C%20and%20I%20appreciated%20the%20firm's%20high%20expectations%20and%20learned%20a%20lot%20from%20my%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20several%20aspects%20of%20my%20job%20frustrated%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20an%20expectation%20that%20everything%20needed%20to%20be%20done%20immediately.%20I%20felt%20a%20constant%20sense%20of%20urgency%20even%20though%20we%20weren't%20building%20anything.%20My%20work%20output%20was%20always%20a%20PowerPoint%20deck%2C%20and%20its%20biggest%20impact%20was%20making%20whoever%20paid%20for%20us%20to%20be%20there%20look%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20an%20environment%2C%20you%20quickly%20realize%20that%20everything%20is%20political.%20Your%20ability%20to%20get%20on%20good%20projects%2C%20and%20even%20your%20performance%20goals%2C%20boil%20down%20to%20how%20well-liked%20you%20are%20by%20colleagues.%20Everyone%20at%20the%20firm%20can%20do%20the%20work%20so%20well%20that%20the%20higher-ups%20ultimately%20build%20teams%20of%20people%20they%20like%20working%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20firm%20had%20clearly%20over-hired%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20biggest%20issue%20was%20that%20McKinsey%20over-predicted%20how%20much%20work%20I%20would%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20at%20the%20firm%20in%20June%202021%20as%20one%20among%20a%20class%20of%20pandemic%20hires.%20I%20left%20in%20March%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20time%2C%20McKinsey%20secured%20many%20government%20and%20private%20sector%20contracts%20and%20hired%20extensively%2C%20assuming%20there%20would%20be%20a%20steady%20workflow.%20Then%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-do-interest-rate-hikes-impact-housing-market-rent-mortgages-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterest%20rates%20started%20rising%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20companies%20started%20tightening%20their%20budgets%2C%20and%20several%20realized%20they%20could%20automate%20much%20of%20their%20work.%20So%2C%20client%20demand%20began%20to%20dry%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20the%20pace%20of%20the%20work%20started%20to%20slow%20down%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%202021%20and%20into%202022.%20Several%20jobs%20at%20the%20firm%20started%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20redundant.%20The%20pressure%20to%20cut%20down%20the%20workforce%20was%20palpable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinsey%20doesn't%20normally%20conduct%20layoffs.%20Instead%20they%20push%20employees%20out%20by%20marking%20them%20down%20on%20performance.%20But%20the%20communication%20channels%20aren't%20clear%20when%20you're%20an%20entry-level%20employee.%20So%2C%20it's%20possible%20to%20get%20positive%20feedback%20from%20the%20clients%20you're%20working%20with%20and%20your%20direct%20manager%2C%20even%20when%20the%20higher-ups%20are%20trying%20to%20push%20you%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20not%20a%20pleasant%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt%20would%20have%20been%20easier%20if%20they%20just%20laid%20me%20off%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20getting%20a%20call%20in%20mid-February%202023.%20Things%20had%20gone%20pretty%20well%20on%20the%20project%20I%20was%20working%20on%20that%20week%2C%20which%20was%20on%20semiconductors%2C%20an%20pretty%20competitive%20to%20get%20staffed%20on.%20On%20Saturday%2C%20I%20got%20a%20call%20out%20of%20the%20blue%20from%20an%20Associate%20Partner%20who%20told%20me%20I%20was%20no%20longer%20on%20the%20project%2C%20even%20though%20I%20was%20supposed%20to%20go%20to%20Seattle%20that%20Monday%20to%20continue%20work.%20I%20received%20another%20call%20on%20Sunday%20and%20was%20told%20to%20talk%20to%20my%20Senior%20Partner%20because%20there%20was%20some%20hope%20I%20could%20get%20back%20on%20the%20project.%20But%20he%20flat-out%20said%20there%20was%20no%20way%20I%20was%20getting%20back%20on%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20meeting%20put%20on%20my%20calendar%20a%20week%20later%20and%20was%20told%20that%20senior%20managers%20would%20be%20present%20at%20the%20meeting%20to%20decide%20my%20fate%20at%20the%20firm.%20In%20the%20days%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20meeting%2C%20I%20kept%20receiving%20warnings%20that%20it%20wouldn't%20go%20well%20and%20that%20I%20was%20better%20off%20just%20quitting.%20I%20told%20them%20that%20I%20refused%20to%20quit%20before%20going%20through%20with%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20meeting%2C%20they%20complained%20about%20my%20performance%2C%20even%20though%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20the%20real%20reason%20they%20wanted%20me%20out%20was%20because%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmanagement-consulting-firm-mckinsey-plans-to-cut-jobs-reports-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirm%20had%20over-hired%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20would%20have%20been%20easier%20if%20they%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20letting%20you%20go%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BWe're%20firing%20you.%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20they%20told%20me%20that%20the%20senior%20partners%20had%20met%20and%20decided%20that%20my%20next%20step%20was%20%26quot%3Bsearch.%26quot%3B%20I'd%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-offering-staff-pay-career-coaching-if-they-leave-firm-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaid%20for%20six%20weeks%20and%20given%20a%20guidance%20counselor%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20would%20help%20me%20look%20for%20another%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20have%20fought%20it%2C%20but%20I%20was%20pretty%20frustrated%20with%20my%20work%20by%20then.%20My%20biggest%20gripe%20is%20that%20McKinsey%20preys%20on%20people%20who%20are%20status-insecure.%20Everyone%20the%20firm%20hires%20is%20an%20overachiever.%20We%20want%20to%20do%20well%2C%20and%20what%20people%20care%20more%20about%20than%20money%2C%20honestly%2C%20is%20the%20gratification%20of%20our%20bosses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELife%20after%20McKinsey%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20then%20I%20was%20already%20thinking%20about%20solving%20this%20other%20problem%20I%20had%20experienced%20as%20an%20intern%20%E2%80%94%20the%20struggle%20of%20subletting.%20So%20my%20good%20friend%2C%20who%20was%20working%20at%20Apple%20at%20the%20time%2C%20quit%20his%20job%2C%20and%20we%20both%20hit%20the%20ground%20running%2C%20building%20a%20new%20startup%20called%20Ohana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOhana%20fills%20the%20gap%20between%20short-term%20rental%20platforms%20like%20Airbnb%20and%20long-term%20housing%20sites%20like%20Zillow.%20We%20provide%20an%20efficient%20way%20to%20sublease%20in%20NYC.%20We've%20found%20that%20the%20average%20host%20on%20Ohana%20saves%20%245%2C969%20per%20sublease%2C%20and%20in%20the%20last%20month%2C%20Ohana%20has%20saved%20New%20Yorkers%20over%20%24238%2C000%20in%20rent.%20We've%20also%20brought%20on%20some%20heavy-weight%20backers%2C%20including%20Zillow's%20cofounder%20and%20former%20CEO%2C%20Spencer%20Rascoff%2C%20and%20Airbnb's%20former%20director%20of%20Engineering%2C%20Surabhi%20Gupta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20passionate%20about%20the%20work%20I'm%20doing%20now.%20Looking%20back%2C%20the%20irony%20of%20my%20time%20at%20McKinsey%20is%20that%20they're%20constantly%20giving%20right-sizing%20advice%20to%20their%20clients%2C%20but%20completely%20miss%20the%20mark%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20consultant%20in%20a%20tough%20work%20environment%3F%20We%20would%20like%20to