20However%2C%20for%20gardeners%20in%20other%20regions%20you%20need%20to%20test%20your%20soil%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20advises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20this%2C%20she%20recommends%20a%20DIY%20trick%20to%20test%20the%20soil%20consistency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTake%20a%20handful%20of%20soil%2C%20dampen%20it%2C%20and%20try%20to%20shape%20it%20into%20a%20%3Cem%3Eladdu%3C%2Fem%3E.%20If%20you%20can%20easily%20make%20%3Cem%3Eladdu%20%3C%2Fem%3Efrom%20the%20soil%2C%20it%20has%20a%20high%20clay%20content.%20Mix%2020%20to%2030%20percent%20of%20sand%20into%20the%20soil%20till%20it%20crumbles%20and%20falls%20apart.%20Additionally%2C%20also%20mix%2020%20to%2030%20percent%20of%20cow%20dung%20compost%20and%20a%20handful%20of%20neem%20%3Cem%3Ekhali%20%3C%2Fem%3E(cake)%20powder%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr%20Anshu%20suggests%20a%20sandy%20soil%20to%20cultivate%20spices%20like%20bay%20leaf%20and%20saffron.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-1-1712929303-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-347220%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDr%20Anshu%20suggests%20a%20sandy%20soil%20to%20cultivate%20spices%20like%20bay%20leaf%20and%20saffron.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EKnow%20when%20to%20fertilise%20the%20plant%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20we%20have%20already%20added%20cow%20dung%20compost%20and%20neem%20%3Cem%3Ekhali%20%3C%2Fem%3Einto%20the%20soil%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20need%20to%20fertilise%20the%20soil%20frequently.%20Right%20before%2015%20days%20of%20flowering%20season%2C%20add%20a%20handful%20of%20vermicompost%20in%20the%20pot%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHarvest%20spices%20at%20the%20right%20time%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Anshu%20says%20different%20spices%20have%20varied%20stages%20of%20flowering%20and%20production.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20instance%2C%20spices%20like%20cumin%20and%20coriander%20are%20ready%20for%20harvest%20within%20five%20months%20whereas%20black%20pepper%20takes%20two%20to%20three%20years%20and%20cardamom%20takes%20five%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20she%20is%20stocking%20her%20kitchen%20cabinets%20with%20cumin%2C%20%3Cem%3Ekalonji%20%3C%2Fem%3Eseeds%2C%20fenugreek%2C%20and%20fennel.%20Dr%20Anshu%20says%20these%20spices%20have%20a%20distinct%20aroma%20compared%20to%20those%20available%20in%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20use%20of%20chemicals%2C%20harmful%20fertilisers%2C%20colours%2C%20and%20additives%20is%20a%20huge%20concern%20in%20commercially%20packaged%20spices.%20With%20these%20tips%2C%20you%20can%20grow%20your%20own%20spices%20at%20home%20and%20save%20your%20family%20from%20the%20perils%20of%20toxic%20spices%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat.%20All%20photos%3A%20Dr%20Anshu%20Rathi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712930219000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FGardening-2-1712929222.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp